turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why did he invite her here?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, God, line.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why does that bother you?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why does- why, does that bother you?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She's been in New York three and a half years.  Why, all of a sudden--

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, maybe- maybe he just wanted to see her.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Nobody comes seven hundred miles just to see.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What do you mean?  He grew up next door to the girl all his life.  Why shouldn't he want to -- why shouldn't he want to see her again?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Don't look at me like that.  He didn't tell me anymore than he told you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: He's not going to marry her.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: How do you know he's even thinking about it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's got that about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well so what?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What's going on here, Joe?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Line.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Now listen, kid. Now, listen.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh.  Now listen, kid.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She's not his girl, Joe.  She knows she's not.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can't read her mind.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Then why is she still single?  New York is full of men.  Why hasn't she married?  Probably a hundred people told her she's foolish, but she's waited.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: How do you know why she waited?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Because she knows what I know, that's why.  She's faithful as a rock.  In my worst moments, I think of her waiting and I know, again, that I'm right.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Look, it's a nice day.  What are we arguing for?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Nobody in this house dares take her faith away, Joe.  Strangers might, but not his father, not his brother.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What do you want me to do? What do you want?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I want you to act like he's coming back, both of you.  Don't think I haven't noticed you since he invited her here.  I won't stand for any nonsense.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: But, Kate--

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Because if he's not coming back, I'll kill myself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Laugh.  Laugh at me.  But why did that happen the very night that she came here?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She goes to sleep in his bed and his memorial breaks in pieces.  Look.  Look at it.  Joe--

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Believe with me, Joe.  I can't stand all alone

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Only last week, a man turned up in Detroit missing longer than Larry.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Alright, alright.  Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You, above all, have got to believe.  You.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why me above all?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just don't stop believing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What does that mean, me above all?  Look at you.  You're shaking.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I can't help it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What have I got to hide?  What the hell is the matter with you, Kate?
